ysql-engine\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">521</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":521,\"repo\":\"vimeo/php-mysql-engine\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -  A MySQL engine written in pure PHP.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T23:13:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ziadoz/awesome-php","categoryHTML":"<h1>Resources</h1><h3>PHP Websites</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://laravel-news.com/\">Laravel News</a> - The official Laravel blog.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T23:13:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ziadoz/awesome-php","categoryHTML":"<h1>Resources</h1><h3>PHP Websites</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://php.watch/\">PHP Watch</a> - PHP articles, news, upcoming changes, RFCs and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T23:13:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"MartinMiles/awesome-sitecore","categoryHTML":"<h2>Forms</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/afaniuolo/WFFM-Conversion-Tool\">WFFM Conversion Tool</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/afaniuolo/WFFM-Conversion-Tool\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"afaniuolo/WFFM-Conversion-Tool\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A console application that provides an automated solution to convert and migrate Web Forms For Marketers (WFFM) items and their data to Sitecore Forms.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T22:38:04.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ocaml-community/awesome-ocaml","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.cornell.edu/courses/cs3110/2021sp/textbook/\">Functional Programming in OCaml: A Principled Approach</a> - Textbook for CS 3110 Functional Programming in OCaml, Cornell University.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T21:49:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Structures and Modeling</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.infoq.com/articles/unified-data-modeling-for-relational-and-nosql-databases/\">Unified Data Modeling for Relational and NoSQL Databases</a> - Solution for managing both NoSQL and relational databases using the Unified Data Modeling technique.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T20:01:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Graph Databases</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.graphdatamodeling.com\">Graph Data Modeling Visualize Structure and Meaning</a> - Brief introduction to graph data modeling and is an introduction to the book \"Graph Data Modeling for NoSQL and SQL\" by Thomas Frisendal.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T20:01:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Overview of NoSQL</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.umd.edu/~abadi/papers/abadi-cloud-ieee09.pdf\">Data Management in the Cloud: Limitations and Opportunities (PDF)</a> - Abadi (2009) discusses limitations and opportunities of data management and data analysis in the cloud.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:55:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Overview of NoSQL</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://shopify.engineering/five-common-data-stores-usage\">Five Common Data Stores and When to Use Them (2019)</a> - Article describes five common data stores (relational database, non-relational (“NoSQL”) database, key-value store, full-text search engine, message queue) and their attributes.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:55:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Criticisms and Debates</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.bradley-holt.com/2011/07/addressing-the-nosql-criticism/\">Addressing the NoSQL Criticism (2011)</a> - Argues against nine criticisms to NoSQL databases as they apply to CouchDB, but may apply to others as well.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:55:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Overview of NoSQL</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://martinfowler.com/books/nosql.html\">NoSQL Distilled</a> - Very digestable and affordable book describing the different NoSQL databases and help you make the decision on whether using a NoSQL database is appropriate for your project.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Overview of NoSQL</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.baqend.com/nosql-databases-a-survey-and-decision-guidance-ea7823a822d\">NoSQL Databases: a Survey and Decision Guidance (2016)</a> - \"This NoSQL Toolbox allows us to derive a simple decision tree to help practitioners and researchers filter potential system candidates based on central application requirements\".</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Overview of NoSQL</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.prisma.io/dataguide/intro/comparing-database-types\">Comparing Database Types: How Database Types Evolved to Meet Different Needs</a> - Good overview of databases in general and how NoSQL database types differ and can be useful.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"erictleung/awesome-nosql-guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Crowd-Sourced Information</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/nosql/\">/r/nosql</a> - Reddit page on NoSQL on general questions and discussions people may have about NoSQL databases.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:49:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"iCHAIT/awesome-macOS","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Audio</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://plugformac.com\">Plug</a> - Discover and listen to music from Hype Machine. <a href=\"https://github.com/wulkano/Plug\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/iCHAIT/awesome-osx/master/media/oss.svg\" alt=\"Open-Source Software\"></a> <img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/iCHAIT/awesome-osx/master/media/free.svg\" alt=\"Freeware\"></li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T19:36:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ConstructCommunity/awesome-construct","categoryHTML":"<h2>Games Showcase</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.madewithconstruct.com/\">Games made with Construct</a> - A website that list all the games made with the engine.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T16:57:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"godotengine/awesome-godot","categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins and scripts</h2><h4>Various Godot versions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GDQuest/godot-shaders\">Godot Shaders</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/GDQuest/godot-shaders\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1846,\"repo\":\"GDQuest/godot-shaders\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A large library of free and open-source shaders for 2D and 3D.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T16:05:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bitcloudproject.org\">Bitcloud</a> is an open source distributed cloud storage system and escrow agent based on Tahoe-LAFS that allows publishers to pay storage nodes for storing encrypted data and sharing that data with others. The decentralized nature of Bitcloud allows anyone to publish large amounts of data in a way that is free from censorship, high costs, and proprietary software. The first application for bitcloud will be <a href=\"https://github.com/wetube/wetube-web\">WeTube</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wetube/wetube-web\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">52</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":52,\"repo\":\"wetube/wetube-web\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, a platform for viewing and publishing videos, podcasts, ebooks, music, and other forms of media.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://datproject.org\">DAT</a> decentralized file system with live replication</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>The <a href=\"http://drogul.us/\">Drogulus</a> (WIP) is a programmable peer-to-peer data store. It's an open, federated and decentralised system where the identity of users and provenance of data is ensured by cryptographically signing digital assets.<a href=\"http://redecentralize.org/#interviews\">Redecentralise Video interview</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ipfs.io\">IPFS</a> is a new hypermedia distribution protocol, addressed by content and identities. IPFS enables the creation of completely distributed applications. It aims to make the web faster, safer, and more open. IPFS is an open source project developed by the team at Interplanetary Networks and many contributors from the open source community.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.owncloud.org/\">ownCloud</a> is personal cloud software with a focus on ease of use and syncing, mobile clients and a wide range of applications.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://perkeep.org/\">Perkeep (was Camlistore)</a> is your personal storage system for life. It is an acronym for \"Content-Addressable Multi-Layer Indexed Storage\" and could be described as \"Like git for all content in your life\"</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://seafile.com\">Seafile</a> is a cloud software similar to owncloud, with clients for Windows, Mac, Linux, Android and iOS. Server for Linux and Raspberry Pi.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sia.tech\">Sia</a> is the leading decentralized cloud storage platform. No signups, no servers, no trusted third parties. Sia leverages blockchain technology to create a data storage marketplace that is more robust and more affordable than traditional cloud storage providers. Instead of using a centralized provider, peers on Sia rent storage from each other. Sia itself stores only the storage contracts formed between parties, using a Bitcoin-style blockchain.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://swarm.ethereum.org\">Swarm</a> is a distributed storage platform and content distribution service, a native base layer service of the ethereum web3 stack. It uses the ethereum economy to incentivize P2P storage.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tahoe-lafs.org\">Tahoe-LAFS</a> is a Free and Open cloud storage system. It distributes your data across multiple servers. Even if some of the servers fail or are taken over by an attacker, the entire filesystem continues to function correctly, preserving your privacy and security.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://thaliproject.org/\">Thali</a> is an open source personal data store that syncs across one or more of your devices, and (selectively, via one or more apps) to one or more more trusted peers. Data store: Couchbase Lite (open source, NoSQL, multi-master sync). Trust model: public key exchange, mutual SSL authentication. Network transport: HTTPS. P2P mechanisms: local/ad-hoc, or Tor (using hidden services).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud and storage</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.virtkick.io/\">VirtKick</a> is your self-hosted DigitalOcean. Take cloud back to your computer, home network or a dedicated server. Manage virtual machines, Docker containers and create 1-click apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cryptocurrencies and markets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bitcoin.org/en/\">BitCoin</a> is a digital currency, a protocol, and a software that enables it. Decentralized crypto-currency</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cryptocurrencies and markets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/voluntarynet/bitmarkets\">Bitmarkets</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/voluntarynet/bitmarkets\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">109</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":109,\"repo\":\"voluntarynet/bitmarkets\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> a working decentralized marketplace based on bitcoinj and bitmessage.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cryptocurrencies and markets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://bitsquare.io\">Bitsquare</a> Bitsquare is a decentralized bitcoin exchange. It supports national currencies (fiat) with a variety of payment methods as well as alternative cryptocurrencie</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cryptocurrencies and markets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ethereum.org/\">Ethereum</a> is an enhanced cryptocurrency with support for Next-Generation Generalized Smart Contract and Smart Property.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cryptocurrencies and markets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ppcoin.org/\">PeerCoin/PPCoin</a> is the first known cryptocurrency based on an implementation of a combined proof-of-stake/proof-of-work system</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Developer tools and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.j-io.org/\">jIO</a> is a client-side JavaScript library to manage documents across multiple storages, in a modular way, such as LocalStorage, WebDAV, Amazon S3, you name it.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Developer tools and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kademlia\">Kademlia</a> is a distributed hash table for decentralized peer-to-peer computer networks</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Developer tools and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/savoirfairelinux/opendht\">OpenDHT</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/savoirfairelinux/opendht\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">880</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":880,\"repo\":\"savoirfairelinux/opendht\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> is a lightweight C++11 Distributed Hash Table implementation offering a clean and powerful distributed map API. It is used by <a href=\"https://ring.cx\">Ring</a>, is able to listen to value changes and adds a cryptography layer.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Developer tools and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/unsetbit/p\">P</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/unsetbit/p\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">405</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":405,\"repo\":\"unsetbit/p\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> is a small JavaScript library for creating peer-to-peer applications in browsers. It allows for transitive connections across peers which makes certain network topologies, such mesh networks,easy to establish.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Developer tools and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://sharksystem.net/\">Shark</a> is an open source framework for building semantic P2P applications in Java. It facilitates building decentralized application based on the notion of ontologies. The name is an acronym for 'Shared Knowledge'.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Developer tools and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jlund/streisand\">Streisand</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jlund/streisand\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">22.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":22874,\"repo\":\"jlund/streisand\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> sets up a new server running L2TP/IPsec, OpenSSH, OpenVPN, Shadowsocks, Stunnel, and a Tor bridge. It also generates custom configuration instructions for all of these services. At the end of the run you are given an HTML file with instructions that can be shared with friends, family members, or fellow activists.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://thefnf.org/\">The FNF</a> is the free network foundation: teaching how to build wireless community networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://en.freifunk.net\">Freifunk</a> is a non-commercial initiative for free decentralised wireless mesh networks. Technically Freifunk firmwares are based on <a href=\"http://www.openwrt.net\">OpenWRT</a> and OLSR or B.A.T.M.A.N.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://funkfeuer.at/\">Funkfeuer</a> is, just like Freifunk, a non commercial initiative for free wireless mesh networks. Funkfeuer is based in Austria and uses <a href=\"http://www.openwrt.net\">OpenWRT</a> as the firmware for the Routers.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ipop-project.org/\">IPOP (IP-over-P2P)</a> is an open-source user-centric software virtual network allowing end users to define and create their own virtual private networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://librevpn.org.ar\">LibreVPN</a> is a virtual mesh network using <a href=\"http://tinc-vpn.org\">tinc</a> plus configuration scripts that even let you build your own mesh VPN.  It's also IPv6 enabled.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://netsukuku.freaknet.org\">Netsukuku</a> is an ad-hoc network system designed to handle massive numbers of nodes with minimal consumption of CPU and memory resources. It can be used to build a world-wide distributed, fault-tolerant, anonymous, and censorship-immune network, fully independent from the Internet.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nycmesh.net/\">NYC Mesh</a> aims to create a free, resilient, stand-alone communication system that serves both for daily use and also for emergencies—be it power outages or internet disruption—running software that helps our community with hyperlocal maps and events.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.opennicproject.org/\">OpenNIC Project</a> is an alternative DNS provider that is open and democratic.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sudoroom.org/wiki/Mesh\">People's Open Network</a> is a community mesh network in Oakland, California.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networking</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://zeronet.io\">ZeroNet</a> enabled decentralized websites using Bitcoin crypto and the BitTorrent network</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Social Networks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://buddycloud.com\">Buddycloud</a> is built for people who care about their privacy. We are building the future of social networks. A future founded on openness. A future built using open standards. We are making the future happen now, by building a massively scaled and fully distributed social network. Buddycloud is leading a quiet revolution to replace the closed retweet and like incumbents.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Social Networks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://diasporaproject.org/\">Diaspora*</a> is a free social network consisting of personal web server that implements a distributed social networking service. Diaspora* is a fun and creative community that puts you in control.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Telephony</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.servalproject.org/\">The Serval Project</a> lets mobile phones make phone calls to each other peer-to-peer without a base station.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"redecentralize/alternative-internet","categoryHTML":"<h2>Uncategorised</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://wardcunningham.github.io/\">Smallest Federated Wiki</a> innovates in three ways. It shares through federation, composes by refactoring and wraps data with visualization. The project aims to demonstrate that wiki would have been better had it been effectively federated from the beginning, and explore federation policies necessary to sustain an open creative community.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T15:19:53.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>Binary</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CodeIntelligenceTesting/jazzer\">Jazzer</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/CodeIntelligenceTesting/jazzer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">650</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":650,\"repo\":\"CodeIntelligenceTesting/jazzer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A coverage-guided, in-process fuzzer for the Java Virtual Machine. It is based on libFuzzer and can be applied directly to compiled applications.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T14:33:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platform</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://code-intelligence.com\">CI Fuzz</a> - A CI/CD-agnostic platform for feedback-based fuzz testing of both native applications and Java web apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T14:33:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ildoc/awesome-italy-events","categoryHTML":"<h2>October</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>27-28 - <a href=\"https://italy.cyberseries.io/\">ItaliaSec</a> - Milano - This groundbreaking summit is designed for senior security leaders.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T11:17:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ildoc/awesome-italy-events","categoryHTML":"<h2>January</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>27-31 - <a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/\">Global Game Jam</a> - Multiple locations - Get together and create games in one weekend.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T11:15:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ildoc/awesome-italy-events","categoryHTML":"<h2>February</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>21 - <a href=\"https://rome.serverlessdays.io/\">ServerlessDays 2021</a> - Rome - Developer-oriented conference about serverless technologies.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T11:15:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ildoc/awesome-italy-events","categoryHTML":"<h2>February</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>24 - <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/events/aws-innovate/machine-learning/\">AWS Innovate ML &#x26; AI</a> - Online - AI &#x26; Machine Learning with AWS.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T11:15:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ildoc/awesome-italy-events","categoryHTML":"<h2>March</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>2-4 - <a href=\"https://myignite.microsoft.com/home\">Microsoft Ignite</a> - Online - Microsoft annual conference.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-11T11:15:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ildoc/awesome-italy-events","categoryHTML":"<h2>Marc